1
00:04:52,440 --> 00:04:55,348
孩子们 这里的花更多 过来摘吧
There's some more flowers, kids.
Go pick 'em.

2
00:04:55,488 --> 00:04:57,517
哦……
Yeah!

3
00:05:01,366 --> 00:05:03,395
这朵真漂亮！
That's a pretty one!

4
00:05:04,455 --> 00:05:08,393
-我一朵花都没有
-那就去找一朵吧 那边就有
- I don't have one.
- Well, go look for one, over there.

5
00:05:09,284 --> 00:05:12,152
哦 这朵真漂亮  让我看看
Oh, that's beautiful. Let me look at that.

6
00:05:12,293 --> 00:05:14,322
让我看看
Let me look at that!

7
00:05:15,671 --> 00:05:19,909
你们可以把花带回家给爸爸妈妈 多香啊！
Now you can take them home
to your parents. Don't they smell nice!

8
00:05:26,088 --> 00:05:27,707
你好
Hi.

9
00:05:34,015 --> 00:05:37,503
怎么不把地上的信捡起来 杰弗里？
Too much trouble to pick the mail up
off the floor, Geoffrey?

10
00:05:39,893 --> 00:05:41,922
没听到吗？
Hello?

11
00:05:45,521 --> 00:05:47,550
来看看这朵花
Look at this flower.

12
00:05:53,278 --> 00:05:55,307
别这样！阿塔韦！
All right! Attaway!

13
00:05:59,446 --> 00:06:02,644
知道吗 我想我找到稀罕物了
You know, I think I actually
found something rare.

14
00:06:03,734 --> 00:06:05,103
什么？
What?

15
00:06:05,244 --> 00:06:08,602
这朵花 我想是grex（可能是一种植物）
什么？
- This plant. I think it's a grex.
- A what?

16
00:06:08,743 --> 00:06:12,601
G-R-E-X 是两个不同物种交叉授粉
G-R-E-X. That's when
two species cross-pollinate

17
00:06:12,741 --> 00:06:15,609
产生的第三种独特的物种
and produce a third
completely unique one.

18
00:06:15,750 --> 00:06:17,739
听听注释：
And listen to this:

19
00:06:17,869 --> 00:06:24,656
Epilobic 来源于希腊语的epi  
在……之上 或者 是指一种豆荚类植物
"Epilobic, from the Greek epi: upon,
and lobos: a pod."

20
00:06:24,917 --> 00:06:28,855
很多品种都是危险的野草 避免接触
"Many of the species are dangerous
weeds and should be avoided."

21
00:06:29,006 --> 00:06:30,275
危险？
Dangerous?

22
00:06:30,425 --> 00:06:32,454
对于花园来说
In the garden.

23
00:06:32,844 --> 00:06:35,962
看到没？ 这么快就扎根了
See? Look how quickly it roots.

24
00:06:36,093 --> 00:06:39,581
他们在欧洲很多饱经战火的城市
"Their rapid and widespread growth
was even observed

25
00:06:39,722 --> 00:06:42,551
快速的生长和广泛的分布已经引起注意
in many of the war-torn cities of Europe."

26
00:06:42,681 --> 00:06:46,669
确实 这类植物中的一些在被破坏的地表生长的很好
"lndeed, some of these plants
may thrive on devastated ground."

27
00:06:46,809 --> 00:06:50,497
我们周末出去维尔怎么样？周五就上飞机 嗯？
Why don't we go up to Vail
for the weekend? Fly up Friday, hm?

28
00:06:50,648 --> 00:06:52,507
好吧 也许……没问题
OK, maybe. Sure.

29
00:06:53,067 --> 00:06:55,925
杰弗里！我正看书呢！
Geoffrey! I'm trying to read!

30
00:06:56,066 --> 00:06:57,725
你心情不错嘛
You're in a good mood.

31
00:06:57,855 --> 00:07:01,263
我等着看晚上的季后赛呢
Well, I got something
to look forward to tonight - playoffs.

32
00:07:01,404 --> 00:07:03,313
杰弗里！
Geoffrey.

33
00:07:03,443 --> 00:07:06,311
-怎么啦？
-我正看书呢
- What?
- I'm reading.

34
00:07:06,692 --> 00:07:09,850
好吧！我会戴上耳机的 好了 满意了吧？
OK! I'll put the earphones on.
There, see? Happy?

35
00:07:09,991 --> 00:07:12,390
算了 我去楼下看书
Never mind. I'll go downstairs.

36
00:07:16,909 --> 00:07:19,478
开门 Qui est l?
谁？
Comment? Qui est l?
Who is it?

37
00:07:19,618 --> 00:07:21,657
卫生署
Department of Health.

38
00:07:25,706 --> 00:07:28,784
晚安 贝纳尔先生 见到你真高兴
Bonsoir, Monsieur Bennell.
How nice to see you.

39
00:07:50,307 --> 00:07:52,336
那是什么东西？
What is that supposed to be?

40
00:07:52,476 --> 00:07:55,215
这是塞尔韦勒炖鱼
It is cervelles en matelote.

41
00:07:55,355 --> 00:07:58,383
说英语 这东西是什么做的？
In English, what would I be eating
if I ate that?

42
00:07:58,524 --> 00:08:02,682
哦 是把小牛的脑子放在红酒里煮
除了红酒还有什么？
- Ah. Calves' brains in red wine.
- Red wine and what else?

43
00:08:02,813 --> 00:08:07,641
玉米 这可不能说 这是秘密 贝纳尔先生
Mais, c'est impossible. It's impossible.
It's a secret, Mr Bennell.

44
00:08:07,781 --> 00:08:11,939
卫生署可不管什么秘密不秘密的 亨利
You don't have any secrets
from the Department of Health, Henri.

45
00:08:12,069 --> 00:08:15,187
要用勃艮第葡萄酒 牛高汤
A good young Burgundy, brown stock,

46
00:08:15,328 --> 00:08:18,276
百里香 欧芹-一小支
thyme, parsley - just a sprig.

47
00:08:18,407 --> 00:08:22,615
刺山柑 新鲜的月桂叶和大蒜
Capers,... a fresh bay leaf, and garlic.

48
00:08:23,535 --> 00:08:26,074
就这些？
是 是的
- That's all?
- Oui. Yes.

49
00:08:35,421 --> 00:08:37,450
这是什么？
刺山柑
- What is that?
- A caper.

50
00:08:38,670 --> 00:08:39,659
不对
No.

51
00:08:39,800 --> 00:08:42,419
那你说这是什么呢？
Do you presume to tell us
what is in this stock?

52
00:08:42,549 --> 00:08:45,248
这是老鼠屎
什么
- It's a rat turd.
- A what?

53
00:08:45,388 --> 00:08:47,417
老鼠屎
A rat turd.

54
00:08:47,927 --> 00:08:49,966
刺山柑！
老鼠屎！
- A caper!
- A rat turd.

55
00:08:51,186 --> 00:08:52,505
刺山柑！
A caper!

56
00:08:53,555 --> 00:08:55,594
如果这是刺山柑
If it's a caper,

57
00:08:55,724 --> 00:08:57,763
吃吃看
eat it.

58
00:09:03,811 --> 00:09:07,349
我要吊销你的执照 亨利
I'm gonna bring you up
for permit revocation, Henri.

59
00:09:07,480 --> 00:09:11,888
你做的这些烂东西可值不了这么多钱
You're charging way too much
to be serving crap like that in here.

60
00:09:12,028 --> 00:09:16,146
但是 先生 这是意外 你知道我们有多小心的
But, Monsieur, it is an accident.
You know how careful we are.

61
00:10:10,988 --> 00:10:11,977
你好？
Hello?

62
00:10:12,107 --> 00:10:13,686
是伊莉莎白吗？
是的
- Elizabeth?
- Yes.

63
00:10:13,817 --> 00:10:15,476
我吵醒你了吗？
不 你好马修
- Wake you up?
- No. Hi, Matthew.

64
00:10:15,616 --> 00:10:17,975
他们把我的车窗打碎了
哦 不！
- They busted the window of my car.
- Oh, no!

65
00:10:18,115 --> 00:10:21,353
用一瓶就砸的-连好酒都舍不得用
Threw a bottle of wine at it -
not even good wine.

66
00:10:21,494 --> 00:10:24,522
勇士队赢了 我想你们全家都很高兴吧
The Warriors won,
so I guess your household's happy.

67
00:10:24,663 --> 00:10:26,062
当然了
Yes.

68
00:10:26,202 --> 00:10:28,361
你在干什么？
哦 什么都没干
- What are you doing?
- Oh, nothing.

69
00:10:28,491 --> 00:10:31,030
如果你现在就去睡觉 那你就能早点起
If you go to sleep now,
you can get up early.

70
00:10:31,160 --> 00:10:32,489
哦 马修…
Oh, Matthew...

71
00:10:32,620 --> 00:10:36,778
如果你能在七点半来 那你8点前就能开始测试了
If you can come in at 7.30,
you can run the tests before 8 o'clock.

72
00:10:36,918 --> 00:10:42,036
别说了！马修…别说了 我早晨八点前到不了
Stop! Matthew... stop. I'm not coming in 
before 8 o'clock in the morning!

73
00:10:41,167 --> 00:10:44,915
我必须要给减税听证会点压力
- I gotta force the abatement hearing.

74
00:10:45,046 --> 00:10:48,204
-他们只在星期三才有免费名额
-不行 马修！
- Wednesday's their only free slot.
- No, Matthew!

75
00:10:48,344 --> 00:10:50,293
我八点前肯定到不了！
I will not be there before eight!

76
00:10:50,424 --> 00:10:53,542
你知道我提名你做年度明星公务员吗？
I nominated you for
Civil Servant of the Year award.

77
00:10:53,673 --> 00:10:55,712
真的 我想你能通过
It's true. I think you'll win.

78
00:10:55,842 --> 00:11:00,910
好好好 我七点半一定到 
我会帮你做沙门氏菌测试的
OK, OK, OK. I'll be in at 7.30.
I'll run a salmonella test for you.

79
00:11:01,060 --> 00:11:03,129
谢谢 明早见
Thank you. See you in the morning.

80
00:11:03,269 --> 00:11:05,468
晚安 明天见
Good night. I'll see you in the morning.

81
00:11:05,598 --> 00:11:07,717
再见
再见
- Bye.
- Bye.

82
00:12:38,786 --> 00:12:42,074
杰弗里 天啊！你起床多久了？
Geoffrey, my God!
How long have you been up?

83
00:12:42,204 --> 00:12:44,243
没多久
Not long.

84
00:12:45,163 --> 00:12:47,452
你在干什么呢？
What are you doing?

85
00:12:48,372 --> 00:12:50,411
杰弗里？
Geoffrey?

86
00:14:48,120 --> 00:14:52,358
我要罚死他们（法国餐馆） 
这些扇贝是拿切碎的鳐鱼片冒充的
I wanna throw the book at him. Those
scallops are just cut-up pieces of skate.

87
00:14:52,499 --> 00:14:55,238
抱歉 我这就开始测试
I'm sorry. I can start the tests right away.

88
00:14:55,378 --> 00:14:58,246
没什么 这些土豆好像有点不对劲
It's OK...And something's wrong with the potato.

89
00:14:58,376 --> 00:15:01,454
酸奶油也是假的 还有这些韭黄
Either the sour cream is phoney,
or the chives.

90
00:15:01,585 --> 00:15:04,034
对不起 我没有睡过头 都怪杰弗里
I'm sorry. I got up on time.
It was Geoffrey.

91
00:15:04,174 --> 00:15:09,042
这次那个疯牙医有怎么了？
我不知道 他就是很怪
- What did the mad dentist do this time?
- I don't know. He was just weird.

92
00:15:09,173 --> 00:15:11,712
他是疯子 牙医都是疯子
He's crazy. All dentists are crazy.

93
00:15:12,262 --> 00:15:14,711
你晚了吗？
没有
- Are you late?
- No.

94
00:15:15,430 --> 00:15:17,959
他并不是平时的那种古怪
He was weird not the way he usually is.

95
00:15:18,100 --> 00:15:20,579
那肯定是好现象
That can only be an improvement.

96
00:15:22,978 --> 00:15:25,677
这个 不是 这让我很紧张
Well, it's not. It's got me really nervous.

97
00:15:25,817 --> 00:15:27,846
告诉他如果不理发就滚出去
Tell him to shape up or get out.

98
00:15:27,976 --> 00:15:31,014
这是他的家
让他自己选
- It's his house.
- Make him an offer.

99
00:15:31,145 --> 00:15:34,183
你看到这个一定会高兴的
是什么？
- Here's something that'll cheer you up.
- What?

100
00:15:34,314 --> 00:15:36,313
这么近还看不见吗？
Ever seen one of these up close?

101
00:15:36,443 --> 00:15:38,602
这是什么？
你看像什么？
- What is it?
- What does it look like?

102
00:15:38,742 --> 00:15:40,231
刺山柑吗？
是刺山柑吗？
- A caper?
- A caper?

103
00:15:40,362 --> 00:15:41,521
到底是什么？
What is it?

104
00:15:41,651 --> 00:15:44,729
是老鼠屎 但是这汤汁味道还不坏
我帮你捉了只老鼠
- A rat turd, but the sauce was delicious.
- I got you a rat.

105
00:15:44,870 --> 00:15:47,898
你抓到了吗？
我真抓住了 是个大家伙
- Did you find one?
- I've got it. It was a biggie.

106
00:15:48,039 --> 00:15:51,317
这样我们就可以公布他的卫生不良问题了
OK, we'll get a declaration
of "unsanitary" on him.

107
00:15:52,168 --> 00:15:54,197
我们一会再谈好吗？
好的
- I'll talk to you later, OK?
- OK.

108
00:15:54,917 --> 00:15:57,616
还有什么我能效劳的？
没有了 别担心 去吧
- What can I do?
- Nothing. Don't worry. Go on.

109
00:15:57,746 --> 00:15:59,785
抱歉
I'm sorry.

110
00:16:00,255 --> 00:16:02,284
哦 对不起
Oh, I'm sorry.

111
00:16:17,059 --> 00:16:21,627
嗨 说吧 告诉我今天要干些什么
我知道今天的计划
- Hey, come on. Tell me what I've done.
- I understand today's plan.

112
00:16:21,767 --> 00:16:25,175
事出突然 伊莉莎白 我还得再出去一趟
Something's come up, Elizabeth.
I have to go back out again.

113
00:16:25,306 --> 00:16:27,345
现在吗？我们不去看比赛吗？
Now? Weren't we going to the game?

114
00:16:27,475 --> 00:16:29,844
我把票都给了一位病人
The Warriors.
I gave the tickets to a patient.

115
00:16:29,974 --> 00:16:32,343
你今晚不去看比赛了吗？
You're not gonna see tonight's game?

116
00:16:32,483 --> 00:16:34,012
没办法
No choice.

117
00:16:34,153 --> 00:16:36,852
杰弗里 你到底怎么了？
Geoffrey, what is the matter with you?

118
00:16:36,982 --> 00:16:39,431
我没事 只是要去开会
I'm fine. I just have to go to a meeting.

119
00:16:39,571 --> 00:16:41,810
开会？开哪门子会？
Meeting? What kind of a meeting?

120
00:16:41,950 --> 00:16:45,938
伊莉莎白 我想我不需要什么事都跟你汇报吧
Elizabeth, I don't think
I have to justify my every move to you.

121
00:16:46,818 --> 00:16:48,857
杰弗里 这可不像你的风格
Geoffrey, this isn't like you.

122
00:16:49,238 --> 00:16:52,646
别这样 我只是关心你而已
Please, come on. I just want it to be nice...

123
00:16:54,246 --> 00:16:56,725
伊莉莎白 你是怎么回事？
Elizabeth, what's the matter with you?

124
00:16:56,915 --> 00:16:58,944
没什么
Nothing.

125
00:17:34,142 --> 00:17:36,181
请进！
Come in!

126
00:17:37,401 --> 00:17:39,010
嗨
Hi.

127
00:17:39,650 --> 00:17:41,679
还好吗？
How you doing?

128
00:17:50,446 --> 00:17:53,934
疯子是不会感觉到自己发疯的 是吗？
Is it true that if you think
you're losing your mind, you're not?

129
00:17:56,744 --> 00:17:58,773
我希望是这样
Well, I hope so.

130
00:18:01,042 --> 00:18:03,151
我知道这听起来有点荒唐
I know this is gonna sound insane.

131
00:18:03,291 --> 00:18:04,900
什么？
What?

132
00:18:06,420 --> 00:18:09,738
杰弗里不是杰弗里
Geoffrey is not Geoffrey.

133
00:18:10,879 --> 00:18:13,278
你怎么知道？
我就是知道
- How do you know?
- I know.

134
00:18:14,418 --> 00:18:17,496
表面上看 杰弗里还是杰弗里
On the outside Geoffrey is still Geoffrey,

135
00:18:17,636 --> 00:18:20,914
但是 我能感觉到他跟原来不一样了
but on the inside
I can tell there is something different.

136
00:18:21,055 --> 00:18:22,874
有些东西消失了
Something is missing.

137
00:18:23,015 --> 00:18:26,043
是什么？
没有七情六欲 
- What?
- Emotion, feelings.

138
00:18:26,343 --> 00:18:28,382
他已经不是原来的他了
He's just not the same person.

139
00:18:31,811 --> 00:18:34,969
真的 你知道我的意思吗？我知道这听着有点疯狂
Really, you know what I mean?
I know it sounds crazy.

140
00:18:35,100 --> 00:18:38,588
是的 我知道你的意思 我想我知道 吃饭没？
Yeah. I know what you mean, I think.
Have you eaten?

141
00:18:38,729 --> 00:18:40,968
我不饿
吃点芹菜吧
- I'm not hungry.
- Have some celery.

142
00:18:41,108 --> 00:18:42,967
我不…
张嘴 张嘴 张嘴
- I'm not...
- Eat, eat, eat.

143
00:18:45,647 --> 00:18:48,396
我们可以在外面吃 今天月色不错
We can eat outside. It's a beautiful night.

144
00:18:50,275 --> 00:18:52,944
拿着那块肉 好吗？ 切一下
Take that meat there, will you?
Chop it up.

145
00:18:53,074 --> 00:18:56,352
还有把姜递给我 就在那儿 已经切好的那些
And hand me the ginger,
the stuff that's chopped up there.

146
00:19:06,159 --> 00:19:09,817
还有呢 这真的很怪
You wanna know something else?
This is really weird.

147
00:19:12,957 --> 00:19:16,405
我去过他姐姐诺拉那儿 我想跟她说这些事
I went to see his sister Nora to talk to her about it.

148
00:19:17,795 --> 00:19:20,124
但是我开不了口 我忍住了
But I couldn't. I stopped myself.

149
00:19:20,594 --> 00:19:22,083
她也变了吗？
She changed, too?

150
00:19:22,844 --> 00:19:25,043
你觉得我疯了吗？
怎么会
- Do you think I'm crazy?
- No.

151
00:19:27,052 --> 00:19:29,381
你想去看看我的老伙计戴维金博纳
D'you wanna go see my friend David Kibner?

152
00:19:30,721 --> 00:19:32,960
那个精神病学家吗？
不是看病
- The psychiatrist?
- Not like that.

153
00:19:33,100 --> 00:19:35,719
跟他说说 他会给你指点迷津的
Talk to him. He would put things into perspective.

154
00:19:36,979 --> 00:19:39,678
我没疯
不不不 我是认真的
- I'm not crazy.
- No, no, no. I'm serious.

155
00:19:39,808 --> 00:19:44,846
他会结束这一切 不管杰弗里是在外偷情还是玩断臂
He would eliminate whether Geoffrey 
was having an affair, or had become gay.

156
00:19:44,976 --> 00:19:49,844
或者是他染上性病 即使他加入了共和党
Whether he had a social disease,or had become a Republican.

157
00:19:49,984 --> 00:19:54,312
任何让你感到他不同以往的事
All the things that could have happened
to have made you feel he had changed.

