- That not my wife.

179
00:21:44,224 --> 00:21:46,253
你是说她……？
You mean, she's...?

180
00:21:46,723 --> 00:21:48,762
不 不 不一样了
No, no. Different.

181
00:21:53,191 --> 00:21:55,220
她不再是我老婆
That not my wife!

182
00:22:23,580 --> 00:22:25,619
最近怎么样？哈利？
How you doin', Harry?

183
00:22:25,789 --> 00:22:27,828
嗨 小家伙 最近怎么样？
Hey, pooch. How you doin', boy?

184
00:23:11,493 --> 00:23:16,641
你去哪了？我都急疯了 到处都找不到你
Where you been? You've been driving me
crazy. I've been looking all over for you.

185
00:23:16,781 --> 00:23:18,320
怎么了？
What's the matter with you?

186
00:23:19,160 --> 00:23:21,149
没事吗？
You all right?

187
00:23:25,788 --> 00:23:27,827
说话呀 伊丽莎白
Talk to me, Elizabeth.

188
00:24:01,895 --> 00:24:04,054
这些人到处都是
I keep seeing these people

189
00:24:04,854 --> 00:24:06,893
他们互相都认识
all recognising each other.

190
00:24:07,024 --> 00:24:09,563
他们在互相传着些什么
Something was passing between them all.

191
00:24:09,693 --> 00:24:11,722
秘密
Some secret.

192
00:24:15,241 --> 00:24:17,270
这是一个阴谋 我知道
It's a conspiracy. I know it.

193
00:24:17,950 --> 00:24:20,109
哪有什么阴谋
There can't be a conspiracy.

194
00:24:20,329 --> 00:24:23,357
马修 告诉你 这里正在发生着什么事
Matthew, I'm telling you, something's going on here.

195
00:24:23,498 --> 00:24:25,527
一些让我害怕的事
Something that scares me.

196
00:24:25,667 --> 00:24:28,226
我今天想去看杰弗里 想跟他谈谈
I tried to see Geoffrey today,
to talk to him.

197
00:24:28,416 --> 00:24:30,975
他一上午都在自己的办公室里
He's always in his office in the morning.

198
00:25:12,321 --> 00:25:14,350
这真的很怪
It really was weird.

199
00:25:14,490 --> 00:25:17,189
杰弗里跟各种奇怪的人会面
Geoffrey was meeting all sorts of strange people.

200
00:25:17,319 --> 00:25:19,478
互相间传递着什么
Things were being passed between them.

201
00:25:19,618 --> 00:25:22,526
这些人你全都不认识吗？
我都不认识
- None were people you knew?
- I didn't know any of them.

202
00:25:22,657 --> 00:25:25,226
说不定他们都是杰弗里的病人呢
Maybe they were patients of Geoffrey's.

203
00:25:25,366 --> 00:25:28,274
哦 不 不 马修 我知道他们不是病人
Oh, no, no, Matthew. I know they weren't.

204
00:25:28,415 --> 00:25:31,323
我跟着他从镇子的这边跟到那边
I followed him from one end of town to the other,

205
00:25:31,454 --> 00:25:35,822
他走到哪里都要跟这种怪人碰面
and everywhere he went he had these meetings with strange people.

206
00:25:47,548 --> 00:25:50,586
我感觉这样跟踪监视他傻透了
I felt so stupid sneaking around spying on him,

207
00:25:50,717 --> 00:25:53,546
但是我不能跟他说上话 我又能干什么呢？
but I can't talk to him. What can I do?

208
00:25:57,015 --> 00:26:00,673
好吧 金博纳应该能够解释一些事
OK. Well, Kibner will be able
to explain something.

209
00:26:00,804 --> 00:26:02,963
我不需要精神病学家
I don't need a psychiatrist.

210
00:26:03,103 --> 00:26:05,472
忘掉他是精神病学家
Just forget that he's a psychiatrist.

211
00:26:05,602 --> 00:26:08,800
把他当作一个智者 这才是他
Just think of him as an intelligent man, which is what he is.

212
00:26:08,941 --> 00:26:12,559
只是一个读书会 他是名人 非常有名
It's a book party. He's a celebrity.He's very famous.

213
00:26:12,689 --> 00:26:16,017
只要你能忘掉他是精神病学家 你一定会喜欢他的
And you will like him,if you forget that he's a psychiatrist.

214
00:26:16,858 --> 00:26:19,097
我不知道 我不知道
I don't know... I don't know.

215
00:26:19,237 --> 00:26:22,016
马修 我一直住在这里
Matthew, I've lived in this city all my life,

216
00:26:22,156 --> 00:26:25,734
但是今天不知怎么的 我感觉所有东西都不对劲
but somehow today I felt everything had changed.

217
00:26:25,865 --> 00:26:29,063
人都不一样了 不光是杰弗里 是所有人
People were different. Notjust Geoffrey, but everybody.

218
00:26:29,204 --> 00:26:32,192
昨天一切看着都还没挺好的
Yesterday it all seemed normal.

219
00:26:32,992 --> 00:26:35,821
今天虽然表面上看没什么变化 但是实际并不是这样的
Today everything seemed the same, but it wasn't.

220
00:26:35,951 --> 00:26:37,990
这简直是个噩梦
It was a nightmare.

221
00:26:38,870 --> 00:26:40,909
让人直冒冷汗
It really became frightening.

222
00:26:42,879 --> 00:26:46,157
就好象一夜之间整个城都变了
It was like the whole city had changed overnight.

223
00:26:59,513 --> 00:27:03,171
我跟你说过一个英国骆驼军团的故事吗?说过吗?
Did I ever tell you the one
about the English Camel Corps? Did l?

224
00:27:04,511 --> 00:27:07,669
他们困在沙漠里 在撒哈拉
They're trapped in the desert,
in the Sahara desert.

225
00:27:09,140 --> 00:27:13,258
他们被隆美尔包围了40天 吃的没有了
They've been surrounded by Rommel
for 40 days and they've run out of food.

226
00:27:13,398 --> 00:27:17,726
然后统帅赶来对他们做了一个演说
And the captain comes and makes an announcement to the men.

227
00:27:17,857 --> 00:27:19,476
他说
He says,

228
00:27:19,606 --> 00:27:24,394
伙计们 我有一个好消息和一个坏消息
"Men, I have some good news and some bad news for you."

229
00:27:24,654 --> 00:27:27,353
一个人说
等等 你跟我说过这个故事
- One of the men says...
- Wait. You have told me this.

230
00:27:31,492 --> 00:27:33,691
我能再说一遍吗?
Can I tell it to you again?

231
00:27:34,581 --> 00:27:35,820
小心!
Look out!

232
00:27:35,950 --> 00:27:37,609
哦 天啊!锁上门!
Oh, my God! Lock the door!

233
00:27:37,750 --> 00:27:39,779
他们来了!
我们该帮帮他
- They're coming!
- We should help.

234
00:27:39,909 --> 00:27:42,947
救命!救命! 他们来了 他们来了 听啊!
Help! Help! They're coming. They're coming. Listen!

235
00:27:43,078 --> 00:27:45,697
他都吓出屎来了
他真让人害怕
- He's smashed out of his skull.
- He's terrified.

236
00:27:45,837 --> 00:27:49,075
下一个就是你 求求你!求求你!你就是下一个 我们危在旦夕
You're next. Please! Please!You're next. We're in danger!

237
00:27:49,216 --> 00:27:51,115
听我说... 发生了很可怕的事
Listen to me... Something terrible!

238
00:27:51,255 --> 00:27:54,453
求你了 下一个就是你 他们就在这里 他们已经来了!
Please. You're next!Here they are. They're already here!

239
00:27:54,594 --> 00:27:56,083
救命!下一个就是你!
Help! You're next!

240
00:27:56,213 --> 00:28:00,151
他们来了 他们来了
他一定是做了什么
- They're coming. They're coming...
- He must have done something.

241
00:28:05,220 --> 00:28:07,699
警察会帮他的
The policeman'll help.

242
00:28:34,780 --> 00:28:36,819
哦 天啊
Oh, my God.

243
00:28:37,079 --> 00:28:39,938
可怜的人 他刚才说的什么意思？
That poor man.What was he talking about?

244
00:28:40,078 --> 00:28:43,486
到了书店我就打电话把我看到的一切告诉警察
I'll phone a witness report in from the bookstore.

245
00:28:44,626 --> 00:28:48,034
马修 你在这儿太好了!这些人都快把我折磨疯了!
Matthew, thank God you're here! These people are driving me nuts.

246
00:28:48,165 --> 00:28:50,244
我们一起吃晚饭吗?
不 我不能
- Are we gonna have dinner?
- No, I can't.

247
00:28:50,374 --> 00:28:52,453
这儿有电话吗?
在角落里
- Is there a phone?
- Around the corner.

248
00:28:52,583 --> 00:28:56,331
这是伊丽莎白・德里斯科尔 这是杰克・伯利克
这就是那个伊丽莎白吗？
- Elizabeth Driscoll, Jack Bellicec.
- This is the Elizabeth?

249
00:28:56,462 --> 00:28:58,791
这书太烂了 金博纳的书太烂了
The book is awful. Kibner's book is awful.

250
00:28:58,921 --> 00:29:01,540
他的构思一文不值 一文不值
His ideas are garbage. Pure garbage.

251
00:29:01,680 --> 00:29:04,459
你怎么能这么说一个像金博纳这样的人呢？
How can you say that about a man like Kibner?

252
00:29:04,589 --> 00:29:07,338
我不是说像金博纳的人 我就是在说金博纳
Not a man like Kibner. I'm saying it about Kibner.

253
00:29:07,468 --> 00:29:11,666
他每半年就赶出一部书来 我要用半年才能写出一行了
He dashes a book off every six months.
Takes me six months to write one line.

254
00:29:11,807 --> 00:29:14,586
为什么？
因为我字斟句酌
- Why?
- Cos I pick each word individually.

255
00:29:14,726 --> 00:29:18,304
这有什么可炫的？
我又没有跟你说话 不是吗？
- What's so hot about that?
- I wasn't even talking to you, was l?

256
00:29:18,434 --> 00:29:20,833
在莱文沃思街和…
On the corner of Leavenworth and...

257
00:29:20,984 --> 00:29:22,973
特克街
特克街吗？特克街交汇出
- Turk.
- Turk? Turk.

258
00:29:23,403 --> 00:29:25,432
那是他吗？
Is that him?

259
00:29:26,442 --> 00:29:27,851
是的
Yes.

260
00:29:28,481 --> 00:29:29,510
是的！
Yes!

261
00:29:30,780 --> 00:29:34,768
哪有什么好炫的？有什么好炫的？ 我不知道…
"What's so hot about that?
What's so hot about that?" I don't know...

262
00:29:34,909 --> 00:29:38,677
你们应该有记录的 因为那里有一位骑摩托的警官在现场
You must have a report on it
cos there was a motorcycle officer there

263
00:29:38,827 --> 00:29:41,146
