- Everything.

313
00:32:06,007 --> 00:32:08,036
让一下
Excuse me.

314
00:32:12,384 --> 00:32:14,833
我知道你想说什么
I understand what you're trying to say.

315
00:32:14,973 --> 00:32:18,741
我是公共卫生署的伊丽莎白・德里斯科尔 电话联系
My name is Elizabeth Driscoll,the Public Health Department. Call me.

316
00:32:18,892 --> 00:32:20,921
凯瑟琳！走吧 凯瑟琳
Katherine! Come on, Katherine.

317
00:32:23,271 --> 00:32:25,660
那个女人的丈夫不再是他本人了
That woman's husband is not her husband.

318
00:32:25,810 --> 00:32:29,388
我看到过他跟杰弗里在一起 他是他们中的一员 她知道了
I saw him with Geoffrey. He's one of them. She knows about it

319
00:32:29,518 --> 00:32:32,506
没人要帮她 
不是这样的 有人帮她（医生接的话）
- and nobody's helping her.
-That's not ture No. Somebody's helping her.

320
00:32:32,647 --> 00:32:34,846
我很高兴你听到了 戴维・金博纳会帮她的（英文字幕不太对）
I'm glad you heard that. David, Elizabeth.

321
00:32:34,987 --> 00:32:37,136
我都听了一个星期了 现在都流行起来了
I've heard it all week. It's popular.

322
00:32:37,276 --> 00:32:39,555
什么意思 什么流行起来了？
我刚才想要告诉你
- What's that. what's getting popular?
- I was trying to tell you

323
00:32:39,695 --> 00:32:42,514
我也知道有些人……
有些人变了
- that I also know somebody...
- Who's changed.

324
00:32:42,734 --> 00:32:45,403
是的
我们去外边谈吧
- Yes.
- Can we go outside and talk about it?

325
00:32:47,032 --> 00:32:52,370
上面有一位女士 红头发蓝裙子的 她对你的作品很感兴趣
Listen, there's a lady up top - red hair,
blue dress. She's interested in your work.

326
00:32:57,329 --> 00:33:01,067
我这个星期已经从六位病人哪里听过这个该死的故事了
I've heard the same damn story this week from six patients.

327
00:33:01,208 --> 00:33:03,767
人们正在改变 变得没有人性了
People are changing,becoming less human.

328
00:33:03,917 --> 00:33:05,946
这正发生在我们周围
It's happening all around us.

329
00:33:06,086 --> 00:33:08,325
这不是我们要说的
That's not what we're talking about.

330
00:33:08,465 --> 00:33:10,994
这跟与我生活的人没有关系
This has nothing to do with the man I live with.

331
00:33:11,134 --> 00:33:13,743
这当然有关系了 你没看见吗？
It has everything to do with it. Don't you see?

332
00:33:13,883 --> 00:33:19,031
人们聚散匆匆 因为他们不想负责任
People step in and out of relationships
because they don't want responsibility.

333
00:33:19,181 --> 00:33:23,089
所以婚姻都见鬼去了 家庭也支离破碎
That's why marriages are going to hell.
The family unit is shot to hell.

334
00:33:23,220 --> 00:33:26,208
戴维 你没认真听她说
别插嘴！
- David, you're not listening to her.
- Stay out of this!

335
00:33:26,349 --> 00:33:28,338
你看 这就是问题所在
You see, that's the point.

336
00:33:28,478 --> 00:33:31,037
我正听着呢 但是他觉得我没有听 为什么？
I'm listening,but he doesn't think I am. Why?

337
00:33:31,187 --> 00:33:34,875
因为他不认为我会认真对待
Because he doesn't expect me to bother enough, or to care.

338
00:33:35,026 --> 00:33:37,845
伯利克 最后说一遍 停下！
停下什么？！
- Bellicec, for the last time, stop!
- Stop what?!

339
00:33:37,985 --> 00:33:40,724
站住了 安静点 闭嘴
杰克！
- Stand still, be quiet, and shut up!
- Jack!

340
00:33:40,854 --> 00:33:42,223
看了我刚才做的事你有什么感想？
How did you feel about what I just did?

341
00:33:42,363 --> 00:33:43,932
为什么要进商店？他疯了
Why in the store? He's a nut.

342
00:33:44,073 --> 00:33:45,252
你有什么感觉？
How did you feel?

343
00:33:46,072 --> 00:33:48,101
你大概吓到了
You were probably shocked.

344
00:33:48,241 --> 00:33:50,720
你想把你的感官封闭起来
You wanted to shut your feelings off,

345
00:33:50,860 --> 00:33:56,018
或者骗自己什么都没发生 因为这样你就不用面对了
maybe make believe it wasn't happening
cos then you don't have to deal with it.

346
00:33:57,538 --> 00:34:00,237
我想要帮助书店里那个可怜的女人
I wanna deal with that poor woman in the bookstore.

347
00:34:00,367 --> 00:34:02,406
为什么
Why?

348
00:34:02,956 --> 00:34:04,985
你跟她有同感吗？
Do you identify with her?

349
00:34:06,755 --> 00:34:08,364
是的
Yes.

350
00:34:08,794 --> 00:34:10,203
好的
OK.

351
00:34:10,624 --> 00:34:12,203
来吧
Come on.

352
00:34:12,333 --> 00:34:17,041
假如我告诉过你 凯瑟琳正想疏离这段关系
Suppose I were to tell you that Katherine
is trying to escape from a relationship.

353
00:34:17,171 --> 00:34:20,040
他正在对她进行治疗
那他就能把我朝墙上推吗？
- He's treating her.
- So why'd he push me against a wall?

354
00:34:20,180 --> 00:34:21,999
她很不安
她看起来不错
- She's upset.
- She looks fine.

355
00:34:22,140 --> 00:34:24,839
她很不安 杰克
我现在看你倒是挺不安的
- She is upset, Jack.
- You look upset to me now.

356
00:34:24,969 --> 00:34:28,457
帮我个忙 行吗？ 
当然 什么都行
回家去 一会我会给你打电话
Do me a favour, will ya?
Go home and I'll call you later.

357
00:34:28,597 --> 00:34:31,166
回家 让我们单独呆一会
回家？
- Go home and leave us alone for a bit.
- Go home?

358
00:34:31,306 --> 00:34:33,335
行吗？
好的 好的
- OK?
- OK. OK.

359
00:34:33,476 --> 00:34:35,305
谢谢
Thank you.

360
00:34:39,104 --> 00:34:41,433
你正在钻牛角尖
You're jumping to a bizarre conclusion.

361
00:34:41,563 --> 00:34:44,971
你的家人正在变成其他人？
That this man you live with
has been replaced by somebody else.

362
00:34:45,112 --> 00:34:48,180
这听起来更像是你骗自己相信他变了
Isn't it more likely you want to believe he's changed

363
00:34:48,321 --> 00:34:52,059
因为你想要找个借口摆脱他
because you're really looking for an excuse to get out?

364
00:35:02,956 --> 00:35:04,445
我不知道
I don't know.

365
00:35:04,575 --> 00:35:06,654
你能在斟酌一下吗？
Will you think about it, please,

366
00:35:06,794 --> 00:35:08,823
在你要采取什么行动之前？
before you make a move?

367
00:35:08,953 --> 00:35:12,651
在你跳出来并毁掉你所拥有的一切之前 再想想好吗？
Before you jump and destroy something you have. Will you?

368
00:35:13,752 --> 00:35:15,781
好吗？
Please?

369
00:35:20,340 --> 00:35:22,369
好的
Yeah.

370
00:35:28,967 --> 00:35:30,546
谢谢你
Thank you.

371
00:35:30,676 --> 00:35:33,834
我只是在心里上给她贴了一块创可贴 马修
I just gave her a psychological Band-Aid, Matthew.

372
00:35:33,975 --> 00:35:35,964
我应该再多说几句的
I should talk to her some more.

373
00:35:36,104 --> 00:35:39,132
你可以带她来我办公室 明天下午四点左右
You could bring her by my office tomorrow around four.

374
00:35:39,273 --> 00:35:41,172
他到底怎么了？
What's the matter with her?

375
00:35:41,312 --> 00:35:45,050
像是有一种导致幻想的流感正在爆发
It's like there's some kind of hallucinatory flu going around.

376
00:35:45,191 --> 00:35:48,929
人们在一两天之内就会克服 我能做的就是对症下药
People get over it in a day or two. All I can do is treat the symptoms.

377
00:35:49,070 --> 00:35:51,059
她会没事吗？
She's gonna be OK?

378
00:35:51,189 --> 00:35:53,478
睡一宿好觉绝对没有坏处
A good night's sleep wouldn't hurt.

379
00:35:53,608 --> 00:35:55,897
这会传染吗？
哦 马修！
- Is it contagious?
- Oh, Matthew!

380
00:35:56,987 --> 00:36:00,815
把她带回到她男朋友那（大夫想歪了）
你误会了
- Take her home to her boyfriend.
- That wasn't what I was thinking.

381
00:36:00,946 --> 00:36:04,354
我刚才是在想 卫生署有没有必要介入调查
I was just wondering if the Health Department should look at it.

382
00:36:04,494 --> 00:36:06,523
我不知道谁能给出答案
Who knows? I don't know.

383
00:36:07,203 --> 00:36:09,232
我倒是想给出答案
I wish I did.

384
00:36:10,202 --> 00:36:11,691
好吧
OK.

385
00:36:13,121 --> 00:36:15,160
带她回家 马修
Take her home, Matthew.

386
00:36:38,183 --> 00:36:41,211
啊 杰克 读书会怎么样？
Ah, Jack. How was the book party?

387
00:36:43,191 --> 00:36:45,220
那是金博纳的新书吗？
Is that Kibner's new book?

388
00:36:48,899 --> 00:36:50,928
没朗诵你的诗吗？
Didn't get to read your poetry?

389
00:36:52,278 --> 00:36:54,307
对不起 杰克
I'm sorry, Jack.

390
00:36:54,647 --> 00:36:56,686
晚安 这里是伯利克浴室
Good evening. Bellicec Baths.

391
00:36:58,576 --> 00:37:02,934
是的 我们建议在卡利斯托加火山灰泥浆中浸泡15分钟
Yes, we recommend the 1 5-minute soak
in Calistoga volcanic ash,

392
00:37:03,074 --> 00:37:06,352
水波漩涡浴就是这样的
that's followed by an Aqua-Surge whirlpool dip.

393
00:37:23,127 --> 00:37:25,156
嗨 能帮我出来吗？
Hey, can you help me outta here?

394
00:37:27,636 --> 00:37:29,205
伯利克！
Bellicec!

395
00:37:29,345 --> 00:37:31,414
我跟你说话的 帮把手
I'm talking to you. Give me a hand.

396
00:37:31,554 --> 00:37:33,583
帮我出来
Help me outta this thing.

397
00:37:35,473 --> 00:37:37,502
斯坦…
Stan...

398
00:37:37,642 --> 00:37:39,631
每周都有你这样的
Every week we go through this.

399
00:37:39,761 --> 00:37:43,699
为什么你不能配合一下呢？
给我条毛巾
- Why can't you be more cooperative?
- Get me a towel.

400
00:37:43,850 --> 00:37:46,469
你这样会受伤的
You are really gonna get hurt one of these days.

401
00:37:46,599 --> 00:37:48,718
再给我一条毛巾 好吗？
Give me another towel, would you?

402
00:37:48,858 --> 00:37:50,677
别这样
Come on.

403
00:38:03,073 --> 00:38:05,742
南茜 把音乐关了
Nancy, shut the music off.

404
00:38:05,862 --> 00:38:07,941
这是给花放的音乐 斯坦
It's for the plants, Stan.

405
00:38:08,072 --> 00:38:11,270
去他的花 我讨厌音乐
Screw the plants. I hate the music.

406
00:38:11,410 --> 00:38:14,488
这对我的花很有好处 她们喜欢
It's wonderful for my plants.They just love it.

407
00:38:15,709 --> 00:38:18,657
花也有七情六欲的 知道吗 像人一样
Plants have feelings, you know,just like people.

408
00:38:18,788 --> 00:38:23,156
这太神了 这种音乐会刺激植物的生长
It's fascinating. This type of music
stimulates the growth of the plants.

409
00:38:23,296 --> 00:38:25,495
这已经被大量实验所证明
They've done tons of experiments on it.

410
00:38:25,626 --> 00:38:28,455
拜托了 南茜 把音乐关掉
别紧张
- Come on, Nancy. Turn the music off.
- Relax.

411
00:38:28,585 --> 00:38:31,154
太紧张可没法欣赏音乐
You're not gonna enjoy this if you don't.

412
00:39:01,903 --> 00:39:04,931
哦！詹尼先生 你在这儿干什么？
Oh! Mr Gianni, what are you doing here?

413
00:39:05,072 --> 00:39:07,391
伯利克太太 一定要读一下
This is must reading, Mrs Bellicec.

414
00:39:07,531 --> 00:39:09,810
维利科夫斯基的《冲突中的世界》
Worlds ln Collision by Velikovsky.

415
00:39:09,950 --> 00:39:13,358
哦 当然 我看过很多遍了 你看过《造星人》吗？
Oh, yes. I've read that many times. Have you read Star Maker

416
00:39:13,489 --> 00:39:17,067
奥拉夫.斯特普尔顿写的 那个也值得一读
by Olaf Stapledon? That's must reading, too.

417
00:39:18,417 --> 00:39:22,615
好了 实在太晚了 詹尼先生
你真是才女
- Well, it's awfully late, Mr Gianni.
- You're so smart.

418
00:39:22,746 --> 00:39:25,944
哦 詹尼先生 你在泥浆里坐得太久了
Oh, Mr Gianni, you've been sitting in that mud too long.

419
00:39:26,085 --> 00:39:28,454
说不定有点过头了 知道吗
It is possible to overdo it, you know.

420
00:39:29,214 --> 00:39:33,032
哦 对了 谢谢你上次送我的那盆花
Oh, by the way, thank you for that plant
you gave me last time.

421
00:40:04,112 --> 00:40:06,141
我送你进去
I'll walk you inside.

422
00:40:07,280 --> 00:40:09,309
没有必要
You don't have to.

423
00:40:17,077 --> 00:40:19,106
杰弗里？
Geoffrey?

424
00:40:22,625 --> 00:40:24,654
他真体贴
That was sweet of him.

425
00:40:43,218 --> 00:40:45,247
你还好吗？
You all right?

426
00:40:46,177 --> 00:40:48,206
明早见
I'll see you tomorrow morning.

427
00:40:53,934 --> 00:40:57,462
谢谢 马修 你让我感觉好多了
Thank you, Matthew. You've really made me feel better.

428
00:40:57,603 --> 00:41:00,002
我会考虑金博纳的话的
And I'm gonna think about what Kibner said.

429
00:41:00,142 --> 00:41:01,131
好吧
OK.

430
00:41:01,272 --> 00:41:03,181
谢谢你 晚安
Thanks for helping. Goodnight.

431
00:41:03,311 --> 00:41:05,350
再见
See you.

432
00:41:11,778 --> 00:41:13,807
杰克？
Jack?

433
00:41:14,237 --> 00:41:16,266
宝贝 你在哪？
Honey, where are ya?

434
00:41:17,486 --> 00:41:21,524
我不想打断你思考 但是我想去吃中国菜
I don't wanna disturb you if you're
thinking, but I could do with some chinese food.

435
00:41:21,665 --> 00:41:24,324
我一天没吃饭了 哦…
I haven't eaten all day. Oh...

436
00:41:27,453 --> 00:41:29,652
哦 杰克 这样会喘不上气的
Oh, Jack, you're gonna suffocate.

437
00:41:35,040 --> 00:41:36,579
我的鼻子…
My nose...

438
00:41:38,709 --> 00:41:40,748
让我离开！让我离开！
Let me out! Let me out!

439
00:41:40,878 --> 00:41:42,617
我鼻子出血了
My nose is bleeding.

440
00:42:06,819 --> 00:42:08,308
谁呀？
Who is it?

441
00:42:09,278 --> 00:42:11,307
谁呀？
Who is it?

442
00:42:14,487 --> 00:42:16,516
是马修
It's Matthew.

443
00:42:16,656 --> 00:42:19,055
进来吧
怎么了？
- Come on in.
- What happened?

444
00:42:19,195 --> 00:42:20,814
在后边
Back here.

445
00:42:20,944 --> 00:42:23,653
我是把你当朋友才叫你来的
哦 杰克…
- Matthew, I called you here as a friend.
- Oh, Jack...

446
00:42:23,783 --> 00:42:28,571
你是不是负责上报传染病或者有关尸体的事？
Do you report things like contagious
disease or a body in a place of business?

447
00:42:28,702 --> 00:42:30,781
杰克 让他看看吧 
你发现了尸体吗？
- Let him look at it. 
- You found a body?

448
00:42:30,911 --> 00:42:33,610
没有 没什么要紧的
我还以为是杰克呢
- No, not necessarily.
- I thought it was Jack.

449
00:42:34,710 --> 00:42:36,279
是他吗？
Is that him?

450
00:42:36,419 --> 00:42:38,448
是的 单子下面就是
Yeah, under there.

451
00:42:41,127 --> 00:42:43,696
开什么玩笑？
不是玩笑
- What kind of joke is this?
- It's no joke.

452
00:42:44,336 --> 00:42:46,375
这是什么？
What is it?

453
00:42:54,723 --> 00:42:58,211
这他妈到底是什么？！
别冲动 南茜
- What the hell is it?!
- Just keep calm, Nancy.

454
00:42:59,721 --> 00:43:01,760
会传染吗？
Is it contagious?

455
00:43:01,890 --> 00:43:04,259
你的客人看到过吗？
没有
- Did any of your customers see this?
- No.

456
00:43:04,389 --> 00:43:05,758
被人看到我们就完了
It'd ruin us.

457
00:43:05,899 --> 00:43:08,008
我去报警
别这样
- I'm calling the police.
- Don't do that.

458
00:43:08,148 --> 00:43:09,507
为什么？
南茜 别
- Why?
- Nancy, don't.

459
00:43:10,567 --> 00:43:12,596
因为我想杰克是对的
Because I think Jack is right.

460
00:43:13,316 --> 00:43:15,515
这绝不是未成熟个体
It's not immature exactly.

461
00:43:15,655 --> 00:43:17,394
他有张成年人的脸
He's got an adult face.

462
00:43:17,525 --> 00:43:21,433
这是个妖怪 全身都是毛
这不一定
- It's a monster. It's got hair all over it.
- It's vague.

463
00:43:21,783 --> 00:43:23,812
鼻子 嘴唇 头发
Nose, lips, hair.

464
00:43:23,953 --> 00:43:27,691
双手 应有尽有 只是还不完善 没有人格 还没成型
Hands, everything,but no detail, no character. It's unformed.

465
00:43:27,821 --> 00:43:31,189
杰克 别碰  你不知道这是什么
Jack, don't touch it. You don't know where it's been.

466
00:43:32,540 --> 00:43:34,569
没有呼吸
No respiration.

467
00:43:34,709 --> 00:43:36,818
也没有指纹
It's got no fingerprints.

468
00:43:37,248 --> 00:43:39,277
没指纹吗？
No fingerprints?

469
00:43:41,167 --> 00:43:43,196
像个胎儿
Like a foetus.

470
00:43:43,336 --> 00:43:45,365
你刚说过这是成年人
You just said it was an adult.

471
00:43:45,505 --> 00:43:48,204
我说是成年人是因为它很高
I said it was an adult because it was tall.

472
00:43:48,344 --> 00:43:52,082
你多高 杰克？
六英尺四英寸
- How tall are you, Jack?
- Six foot four.

473
00:43:52,213 --> 00:43:55,421
你有多重？
170磅
- How much do you weigh?
- 170.

474
00:43:55,552 --> 00:43:57,921
问这些干什么？
哦 不要
- Why?
- Oh, no.

475
00:43:59,510 --> 00:44:00,999
不要 马修
No, Matthew.

476
00:44:02,219 --> 00:44:04,048
哦 杰克！
Oh, Jack!

477
00:44:04,179 --> 00:44:06,798
你给谁打电话？
伊丽莎白
- Who are you calling?
- Elizabeth.

478
00:44:06,938 --> 00:44:08,967
为什么？
Why?

479
00:44:09,147 --> 00:44:11,346
为什么打给伊丽莎白？
Why are you calling Elizabeth?

480
00:44:11,476 --> 00:44:13,925
马修…
为什么？
- Matthew...
- Why?

481
00:44:25,281 --> 00:44:26,440
喂？
Hello?

482
00:44:26,571 --> 00:44:30,479
伊丽莎白吗？能听见吗？我是马修 伊丽莎白 喂
Elizabeth? Can you hear me? It's Matthew, Elizabeth. Hello?

483
00:44:31,119 --> 00:44:32,358
怎么了？
What's the matter?

484
00:44:32,489 --> 00:44:34,888
伊丽莎白 能听见吗？
Elizabeth, can you hear me?

485
00:44:35,038 --> 00:44:36,857
你是谁？
Who is this?

486
00:44:38,247 --> 00:44:40,276
喂？
Hello?

487
00:45:00,719 --> 00:45:04,087
你去哪儿？
我朋友有麻烦了
- Where are you going?
- A friend of mine is in trouble.

488
00:45:04,218 --> 00:45:06,707
我们该怎么办？
给戴维・金博纳打电话
- What are we to do?
- Phone David Kibner.

489
00:45:06,847 --> 00:45:10,535
让他马上来这儿见我 他的号码
Ask him to meet me here right away. There's his number.

490
00:45:10,686 --> 00:45:12,715
怎么了？
我累了
- What's the matter?
- I'm tired.

491
00:45:13,775 --> 00:45:15,514
起来
Stand up.

492
00:45:15,644 --> 00:45:19,302
站起来！ 四下走走
宝贝儿 我口渴 我渴死了
- Stand up! Now walk around!
- Honey, I'm dry! I'm very dry.

493
00:45:19,443 --> 00:45:22,182
我给你拿点水来 别睡着
I'll get you a drink. Just don't fall asleep.

494
00:45:31,828 --> 00:45:33,437
来 宝贝儿
谢谢 宝贝儿
- Here, sweetie.
- Thanks, sweetie.

495
00:45:33,578 --> 00:45:35,607
金博纳大夫马上就来
Dr Kibner will be here soon.

496
00:45:39,746 --> 00:45:42,025
我要躺下好好想想 宝贝儿
I'm gonna lie down and think, honey.

497
00:45:42,495 --> 00:45:44,534
我就是想点事
I'm just gonna think.

498
00:46:33,827 --> 00:46:35,896
杰克 别睡！ 眼睛！
Jack, wake up! lts eyes!

499
00:46:36,036 --> 00:46:38,855
哦 杰克 它睁眼了
Oh, Jack. It opened its eyes.

500
00:46:50,791 --> 00:46:51,780
看见了吗？
See?

501
00:46:55,000 --> 00:46:55,989
亲爱的？
Hon?

502
00:50:35,524 --> 00:50:36,933
醒醒
Wake up.

503
00:50:37,063 --> 00:50:38,472
醒醒！
Wake up!

504
00:52:45,529 --> 00:52:48,977
我在这儿连个尸体的毛都没看着
I can't find anything in here that looks like a body.

505
00:52:49,108 --> 00:52:50,937
没有尸体？
你说什么！
- No body?
- What!

506
00:52:51,067 --> 00:52:53,896
你查看过最后…
我都找遍了
- Did you check the last...
- I looked everywhere.

507
00:52:54,026 --> 00:52:55,395
嘿！你…… 嘿！
Hey! Did you... Hey!

508
00:52:55,535 --> 00:52:59,303
你查看过左手边最后一个隔间了？
那根本没有尸体
- Did you check the last booth on the left?
- There's no body there.

509
00:52:59,454 --> 00:53:01,483
应该在那儿啊！
It's got to be in here!

510
00:53:04,122 --> 00:53:07,570
它有脉搏、心跳吗?
它睁眼了
- Did it have a pulse, a heartbeat?
- It opened its eyes.

511
00:53:07,701 --> 00:53:11,159
你真的看见了吗？
我看到它鼻子出血了
- You actually saw that?
- I saw its nose bleed.

512
00:53:11,540 --> 00:53:14,448
他的白毛还碰到了我的手
It had white hair, that touched my hand.

513
00:53:14,999 --> 00:53:17,038
那儿有东西
There's something in here.

514
00:53:19,837 --> 00:53:23,205
有一次南茜的一位老年顾客死在这儿 他心脏病发作沉下去了
Nancy lost an old guy in here once.
He had a heart attack and sank.

515
00:53:27,884 --> 00:53:29,543
面对现实吧 伯利克
Face it, Bellicec.

516
00:53:29,684 --> 00:53:32,582
只是你的朋友跟你搞恶作剧而已
You've got some friends who enjoy practical jokes.

517
00:53:32,722 --> 00:53:35,001
我没有朋友 金博纳博士
I don't have any friends, Dr Kibner.

518
00:53:36,101 --> 00:53:38,130
那就是你的敌人
Then some enemies.

519
00:53:38,271 --> 00:53:39,540
看那儿
Look.

520
00:53:43,439 --> 00:53:45,468
谁打开的？
Who opened this up?

521
00:54:10,330 --> 00:54:12,781
等等 等等 谁呀？
Wait a second, wait a second. Who is it?

522
00:54:15,882 --> 00:54:18,503
马修 尸体消失了
有人弄走了尸体
- Matthew, the body's gone.
- Somebody's took it.

523
00:54:18,633 --> 00:54:21,834
不 你没看到吗？
这儿没什么可看的
- No. Did you see it?
- There was nothing here to see.

524
00:54:22,595 --> 00:54:24,795
你想吵醒谁 马修？
Who are you waking up now, Matthew?

525
00:54:24,936 --> 00:54:28,217
警察吗？我发现一具尸体
Police? I would like to report a body.

526
00:54:30,738 --> 00:54:32,728
赶快把她带到我那里去
Take her to my place fast.

527
00:54:32,859 --> 00:54:35,730
在我们回来前别让任何人进来
Don't let anybody in until we get back there.

528
00:55:05,913 --> 00:55:08,394
上尉 他们报告说发现一具尸体
Lieutenant, these fellas reported the body.

529
00:55:08,534 --> 00:55:11,825
你们都看到了吗？
不 只有我看到 马修・贝纳尔
- You both saw it?
- No, I'm the only one. Matthew Bennell.

530
00:55:11,956 --> 00:55:16,077
贝纳尔先生 带我去看看现场吧
就在上面
- Mr Bennell, show me where you saw it.
- It's right up here.

531
00:55:16,338 --> 00:55:18,378
伊丽莎白在哪儿？
Where's Elizabeth?

532
00:55:32,575 --> 00:55:33,985
在哪儿？
在那儿
- Where?
- There.

533
00:55:34,115 --> 00:55:36,275
那是伊丽莎白的替身
哪里？
- It's Elizabeth's double.
- Where?

534
00:55:36,416 --> 00:55:38,366
只是一堆树叶和一个壶
Lots of leaves and a pot.

535
00:55:38,497 --> 00:55:41,908
原本在这的 戴维 我对天发誓
It was there, David. I swear to God it was there!

536
00:55:42,049 --> 00:55:44,870
警官 那是伊丽莎白的复制品
Officer, there was a duplicate of Elizabeth Driscoll,

537
00:55:45,010 --> 00:55:47,250
它被弄走了
那个失踪的女人吗？
- and it's been taken.
- The missing woman?

538
00:55:47,381 --> 00:55:49,251
她没失踪
那她在哪?
- She's not missing.
- Where is she?

539
00:55:49,392 --> 00:55:51,783
她在马修那儿
别说出来
- She's at Matthew's.
- Don't tell him that!

540
00:55:51,933 --> 00:55:54,504
那就是说没有什么失踪的尸体了
当然
- Then there is no missing body.
- That's right.

541
00:55:54,644 --> 00:55:57,265
有的 被他弄走了！
不 他带走了伊丽莎白
- There is and he's taken it!
- No, he took Elizabeth.

542
00:55:57,395 --> 00:55:59,145
你带走了伊丽莎白？
是的！
- You took Elizabeth away?
- Yes!

543
00:55:59,276 --> 00:56:02,317
你破门而入
我必须这样 她在这不安全
- You broke in here.
- I had to because she was not safe here.

544
00:56:02,447 --> 00:56:03,937
这么说你把她从这带走了
So you took her out of here.

545
00:56:04,078 --> 00:56:08,069
不！我把她从这儿带走 她的另一个身体还在这儿
No! I took her from there. Her other body was in here...

546
00:56:08,210 --> 00:56:10,881
别说了 马修 够了 别说了
Please stop. Matthew, that's enough! Please stop!

547
00:56:11,001 --> 00:56:14,122
上尉 我是戴维・金博纳博士
哦 那个精神病专家
- Lieutenant, I'm Dr David Kibner.
- Ah, the psychiatrist.

548
00:56:14,252 --> 00:56:15,912
我妻子看过你的书 她受益良多
My wife reads your books.

549
00:56:16,053 --> 00:56:18,584
我很荣幸 这听着可能有点复杂
戴维……
- I'm glad. It sounds complicated,...
- David...

550
00:56:18,724 --> 00:56:22,665
…但是我的朋友最近被他的感情所困扰
..but my friend has had some difficult 
emotional experiences recently.

551
00:56:22,806 --> 00:56:26,887
但是我想我们自己私下能处理
But I think this is something
we can work out amongst ourselves.

552
00:56:27,028 --> 00:56:30,719
好的 那我就不管了
感激不尽
- All right, I'll leave this part of it with you.
- I appreciate it.

553
00:56:30,859 --> 00:56:34,070
你不能再在这纠缠下去了 我们出去说
You can't accomplish anything here. We gotta get outside.

554
00:56:35,952 --> 00:56:41,074
我想你可能会考虑起诉贝纳尔非法入侵
I think you might wanna consider filing
an unlawful entry against Mr Bennell.

555
00:56:41,214 --> 00:56:43,534
我知道你要说什么 但是外面……
I know what you're saying, but outside...

556
00:56:43,675 --> 00:56:48,006
不 我相信金博纳教授说的 伊丽莎白没事
No, I'll take Dr Kibner's word that Elizabeth is all right.

557
00:56:48,727 --> 00:56:51,178
好吧 我们走吧
好的
- Fine, then let's go.
- OK.

558
00:56:55,320 --> 00:56:57,350
伊丽莎白会回家吗？
Will Elizabeth be coming home?

559
00:56:58,901 --> 00:56:59,891
不
No.

560
00:57:01,413 --> 00:57:03,774
我得给她带几件衣服
I have to pick up some of her clothes.

561
00:57:07,295 --> 00:57:08,035
好吧
All right.

562
00:57:37,088 --> 00:57:40,119
好吧 我们退回去再回想一次
All right, let's back up
and go through it once more,

563
00:57:40,259 --> 00:57:42,539
慢慢来
step by step.

564
00:57:44,431 --> 00:57:47,462
你们都觉得在浴室里看到了尸体
You all thought you saw a body at the baths.

565
00:57:47,602 --> 00:57:50,883
你们想它可能已经死了 你们不知道它是什么
You thought it was dead. You didn't know what it was.

566
00:57:53,145 --> 00:57:56,146
你们都接触过它了 所有人
You touched it. All of you touched it.

567
00:57:59,407 --> 00:58:03,738
南茜 你看到它睁开眼睛
它正好盯着我看
- Nancy, you saw it open its eyes.
- It looked right at me.

568
00:58:05,710 --> 00:58:09,531
伯利克你也看到它睁眼了
不 我看到它鼻子出血
- And, Bellicec, you saw its eyes open.
- No, I saw its nose bleed.

569
00:58:09,672 --> 00:58:13,003
如果你看到它鼻子出血 南茜看到他睁开眼睛
If you saw its nose bleed, and Nancy saw its eyes open,

570
00:58:13,133 --> 00:58:14,963
那它一定活着
he must have been alive.

571
00:58:17,475 --> 00:58:21,136
不 戴维 你是按照人的标准来判断的 但是它不是人
No, David. You're looking at it
as if it was human. It was not human.

572
00:58:22,317 --> 00:58:25,978
马修 那它还能是什么？
不管是什么 绝对不是人
- Matthew, what else would it be?
- It was something, but not human.

573
00:58:26,109 --> 00:58:28,359
他身上有白毛 
它一直在生长
- It had white hair on it. 
- It was growing.

574
00:58:28,490 --> 00:58:30,070
杰克家里的那个像…
The one at Jack's was...

575
00:58:30,200 --> 00:58:33,861
像杰克 但是没有伊丽莎白家的那个成熟
It was like Jack, but not as developed
as the one at Elizabeth's place.

576
00:58:34,002 --> 00:58:35,822
它还有卷胡子
It had tendrils on it.

577
00:58:35,963 --> 00:58:38,033
她家那个是复制她
The one at her place was duplicating her.

578
00:58:38,174 --> 00:58:40,204
如果马修没有把我带走
If Matthew hadn't taken me away,

579
00:58:40,345 --> 00:58:43,916
发生在杰弗里身上的事  就会在我身上重演
the same thing that's happened
to Geoffrey would have happened to me.

580
00:58:44,056 --> 00:58:48,547
伊丽莎白 能跟我说说 在你印象中 到底发生了什么吗？
Elizabeth, would you please tell me, in
your opinion, exactly what is happening?

581
00:58:51,650 --> 00:58:53,810
大家都被复制了
People are being duplicated.

582
00:58:54,941 --> 00:58:58,312
一旦你被复制 你就变成它的一部分
And once it's happened to you, you're part of this thing.

583
00:58:59,703 --> 00:59:01,443
这差点就发生在我身上！
It almost happened to me!

584
00:59:02,954 --> 00:59:04,444
听着
Look,

585
00:59:04,585 --> 00:59:09,657
你不相信伊丽莎白  是因为尸体消失了
the reason you don't believe Elizabeth
is because the other body disappeared.

586
00:59:09,797 --> 00:59:12,838
因为被杰弗里弄走了
It disappeared because Geoffrey took it.

587
00:59:12,969 --> 00:59:15,640
好吧 那我的替身都怎么样了？
Well, then what happened to my other body, then?

588
00:59:15,770 --> 00:59:18,511
哦 伙计 能听听自己在说什么吗？
Oh, people, will you please listen to yourselves?

589
00:59:18,641 --> 00:59:20,801
你们能听听自己在说什么吗？
Will you listen to what you are saying?

590
00:59:20,942 --> 00:59:25,854
我能想象一具尸体被转移  甚至是尸体站起来自己离开
I can deal with a body being moved and
even with a body getting up and leaving,

591
00:59:25,984 --> 00:59:29,765
但是当你说他的另一个身体 
 她的另一个身体 被复制…
but when you start talking about his other 
body,her other body, being duplicated...

592
00:59:29,916 --> 00:59:31,606
知道这到底有多荒谬吗？
Listen to how that sounds.

593
00:59:31,747 --> 00:59:35,198
我们知道这听起来有多疯狂！但是你觉得我们现在在干什么？
We know how insane this sounds!
But what do you think we're doing?

594
00:59:35,338 --> 00:59:36,800
你觉得我们编造了一切吗？
Do you think we're making it up?

594
00:59:36,801 --> 00:59:37,628
你到底是哪里听不懂


595
00:59:37,629 --> 00:59:41,920
你相信我的替身看起来像我 她的替身看起来象她吗？
Do you believe that my body looked like
me and that her body looked like her?

596
00:59:42,051 --> 00:59:43,711
你觉得我们疯了吗？
D'you think we're crazy?

597
00:59:43,852 --> 00:59:48,980
你为什么想说服我们  这只是我们想象出来的？
You are trying to make us believe
that we are seeing things. Why?

598
00:59:48,984 --> 00:59:51,345
我只是想要帮忙
All I'm trying to do is help.

599
00:59:51,485 --> 00:59:55,686
你半夜打电话给我 找我帮忙 我就是来帮忙的
You call me in the middle of the night and
ask me to help. That's all I'm trying to do.

600
00:59:55,827 --> 00:59:57,817
好吧 如果我们吵醒了你 那么对不起
Well, I'm sorry if we woke you up!

601
00:59:57,948 --> 01:00:01,279
如果我们打搅你了 那我们很抱歉
If we inconvenienced you, I guess we owe you an apology.

602
01:00:01,419 --> 01:00:04,780
我是说… 我想这么做很不好！
I mean, I mean... I guess that's a rotten thing to do!

603
01:00:06,592 --> 01:00:08,622
但是你也把我太太搅得心神不宁
You've upset my wife, too.

604
01:00:15,015 --> 01:00:17,926
戴维 我不知道它是什么 或者它从哪来
David, I don't know what it is or where it comes from,

605
01:00:18,066 --> 01:00:20,096
但是我看到了  而且我要给它点颜色
but I saw it and I'm gonna fight it.

606
01:00:20,237 --> 01:00:23,518
马修 老伙计 我相信你
Matthew, my friend,... I believe you.

607
01:00:24,949 --> 01:00:27,480
我们认识这么久 让我怎么能不相信你呢
I've known you too long not to believe you.

608
01:00:27,621 --> 01:00:29,651
你想怎么做？
What do you wanna do?

609
01:00:29,791 --> 01:00:34,112
如果我能得到官方的支持 我得启动应急预案
Well, if I could get official support,
I'd institute the emergency procedures

610
01:00:34,253 --> 01:00:37,034
就是我们针对疟疾和军团热所制定的预案
that we use for cholera or legionnaires' disease.

611
01:00:37,175 --> 01:00:41,006
你想要我做什么？
我想我能搞定健康署
- What do you want me to do?
- I can handle the Health Department.

612
01:00:41,136 --> 01:00:44,627
但是如果引起恐慌  我们需要警察和保安
But if panic breaks out, we'll need the police and the Guard,

613
01:00:44,768 --> 01:00:46,928
就是说市长
and that means the Mayor and...

614
01:00:47,939 --> 01:00:50,510
市长在你那看病 是吗？
The Mayor's a patient of yours, isn't he?

615
01:00:51,281 --> 01:00:53,311
你怎么知道的？
How did you know that?

616
01:00:54,242 --> 01:00:56,272
你想要我做什么？
What do you want me to do?

617
01:00:56,413 --> 01:00:58,864
你能说服他接我的电话吗？
Would you ask him to accept my telephone call?

618
01:00:58,994 --> 01:01:01,365
我会在一个小时内给他打电话 我在办公室
I'll call him in a hour. I'll be at my office.

619
01:01:01,505 --> 01:01:04,066
如果你有其他主意 随时跟我联系
If you have any other ideas, get in touch.

620
01:01:06,547 --> 01:01:08,587
我等你电话
Call me.

621
01:01:09,889 --> 01:01:11,919
谢谢
Thank you.

622
01:01:37,340 --> 01:01:39,380
速战速决
The sooner the better.

623
01:01:42,062 --> 01:01:43,842
真好闻
This smells lovely.

624
01:01:43,973 --> 01:01:47,184
我想要你听我说
我听着呢 南茜
- I want you to listen to me.
- I am listening to you, Nancy.

625
01:01:47,315 --> 01:01:51,006
我没有看错  我知道我看见的是什么
I am not seeing things. I know I saw what I saw

626
01:01:51,156 --> 01:01:55,017
我也知道那东西正变成你  杰克  现在我们发现的尸体…
and I know it was turning into you, Jack.
Now, that body we found...

627
01:01:55,158 --> 01:01:57,488
这花是从哪摘的？
That flower. Where did you get that?

628
01:01:57,619 --> 01:02:00,700
花瓶里
是夹在花中间吗
- In the vase with the others.
- Just stuck in there?

629
01:02:00,830 --> 01:02:04,201
是 怎么了？
杰弗里昨晚也给了我一支这样的
- Yeah. Why?
